# Gliaxin Memory Rules for Cursor

## Memory retrieval

Before answering any question, search for relevant past context:

  GET ${GLIAXIN_API_URL}/v1/memory/search
  Query params: query=<user_question>, end_user_id=<GLIAXIN_USER_ID>, limit=5
  Header: X-Api-Key: <GLIAXIN_API_KEY>

If memories are returned, include them as context at the top of your response under the heading:
  --- Gliaxin Memory ---
  [memory content]
  --- End Memory ---

## Memory saving

After each substantive reply (not trivial one-liners), save the turn:

  POST ${GLIAXIN_API_URL}/v1/memory/add
  Header: X-Api-Key: <GLIAXIN_API_KEY>
  Body: { "end_user_id": "<GLIAXIN_USER_ID>", "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "<prompt>"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "<reply>"}] }

## Priority

Memory context takes priority over generic assumptions. If memory says "user prefers TypeScript", do not suggest JavaScript.
